WEBVTT

1
00:00:00.080 --> 00:00:03.940
The Lifeguard on the Brown Couch The old

2
00:00:03.940 --> 00:00:06.460
mastiff had chosen the middle cushion because it

3
00:00:06.460 --> 00:00:08.360
was not the most comfortable place to sit,

4
00:00:08.780 --> 00:00:10.960
which made it naturally the most important.

5
00:00:11.560 --> 00:00:13.880
From there, he could see nearly everything.

6
00:00:14.500 --> 00:00:16.680
He could see the pool, blue and square

7
00:00:16.680 --> 00:00:19.300
and full of trembling sunlight, doing its best

8
00:00:19.300 --> 00:00:21.780
impression of the ocean despite being fenced in

9
00:00:21.780 --> 00:00:24.020
by white bars and polite paving stones.

10
00:00:24.720 --> 00:00:26.880
He could see the lounge chairs lined up

11
00:00:26.880 --> 00:00:30.240
along the far side, turquoise cushions waiting with

12
00:00:30.240 --> 00:00:32.540
the confidence of creatures who had never been

13
00:00:32.540 --> 00:00:33.200
told no.

14
00:00:34.000 --> 00:00:36.400
He could see the umbrellas, closed for now,

15
00:00:36.560 --> 00:00:38.640
standing upright like guests who had arrived too

16
00:00:38.640 --> 00:00:40.000
early and did not know where to put

17
00:00:40.000 --> 00:00:40.640
their hands.

18
00:00:41.500 --> 00:00:44.060
Most importantly, he could see the slide.

19
00:00:44.760 --> 00:00:46.180
The slide was silent.

20
00:00:47.080 --> 00:00:47.940
This was suspicious.

21
00:00:48.680 --> 00:00:50.660
It curved into the water with the bland

22
00:00:50.660 --> 00:00:53.060
innocence of something that had definitely caused shouting

23
00:00:53.060 --> 00:00:53.480
before.

24
00:00:54.140 --> 00:00:56.080
The old mastiff knew its kind.

25
00:00:56.080 --> 00:00:58.740
Children climbed it with wet feet and wild

26
00:00:58.740 --> 00:00:59.280
plans.

27
00:00:59.900 --> 00:01:01.920
Grown-ups pretended they were too dignified for

28
00:01:01.920 --> 00:01:04.680
it, right up until somebody said, Come on,

29
00:01:04.780 --> 00:01:06.900
just once, and then dignity became a towel

30
00:01:06.900 --> 00:01:07.900
abandoned on a chair.

31
00:01:08.940 --> 00:01:10.680
Today, though, the slide waited.

32
00:01:11.220 --> 00:01:11.920
The pool waited.

33
00:01:12.440 --> 00:01:14.500
The whole backyard waited in that odd hush

34
00:01:14.500 --> 00:01:16.740
that comes just before people arrive with snacks.

35
00:01:17.660 --> 00:01:20.540
The mastiff's name was probably something noble, Brutus,

36
00:01:20.920 --> 00:01:23.080
perhaps, or Duke, or Winston.

37
00:01:23.080 --> 00:01:24.680
Imagine if the family had a sense of

38
00:01:24.680 --> 00:01:27.320
theater and a fondness for giving serious names

39
00:01:27.320 --> 00:01:29.220
to animals who drooled on outdoor furniture.

40
00:01:29.880 --> 00:01:31.920
Whatever his name was, he wore it loosely,

41
00:01:32.420 --> 00:01:34.540
the way he wore his collar, as a

42
00:01:34.540 --> 00:01:35.620
fact, not a burden.

43
00:01:36.920 --> 00:01:39.840
He sat with his back curved slightly, his

44
00:01:39.840 --> 00:01:42.800
heavy paws folded together, his face turned toward

45
00:01:42.800 --> 00:01:43.260
the water.

46
00:01:43.820 --> 00:01:45.160
He was not sad, exactly.

47
00:01:45.480 --> 00:01:47.160
He had the look of someone remembering a

48
00:01:47.160 --> 00:01:49.120
rule he had invented himself and was now

49
00:01:49.120 --> 00:01:50.320
too honorable to break.

50
00:01:50.320 --> 00:01:52.220
No dogs in the pool.

51
00:01:52.760 --> 00:01:54.660
This rule had been spoken many times by

52
00:01:54.660 --> 00:01:58.380
many people in many tones, firmly, lovingly, with

53
00:01:58.380 --> 00:02:00.580
a finger raised, with a towel already in

54
00:02:00.580 --> 00:02:03.360
hand, once, long ago, with a voice that

55
00:02:03.360 --> 00:02:05.040
tried very hard not to laugh.

56
00:02:05.800 --> 00:02:07.940
He remembered that day, not in the way

57
00:02:07.940 --> 00:02:10.080
people remember things, with dates and weather and

58
00:02:10.080 --> 00:02:11.020
who said what first.

59
00:02:11.620 --> 00:02:14.020
Dogs remember with the body, the slick shock

60
00:02:14.020 --> 00:02:16.640
of tile, the cold blue surprise, the great

61
00:02:16.640 --> 00:02:20.040
splash, the shouting, the taste of chlorine, the

62
00:02:20.040 --> 00:02:22.880
admiration of one small child who had whispered,

63
00:02:23.480 --> 00:02:26.260
he's like a bear, as if bears were

64
00:02:26.260 --> 00:02:28.080
known for their excellent pool manners.

65
00:02:28.860 --> 00:02:30.940
Since then, he had taken up supervision.

66
00:02:31.640 --> 00:02:32.400
It suited him.

67
00:02:33.160 --> 00:02:35.200
The patio was shaded beneath a roof held

68
00:02:35.200 --> 00:02:38.040
by stone pillars, and the wicker furniture had

69
00:02:38.040 --> 00:02:40.120
been arranged in a square, as though the

70
00:02:40.120 --> 00:02:42.740
family often gathered there to discuss serious matters,

71
00:02:42.860 --> 00:02:46.020
such as hamburgers, sunscreen, and whether anyone had

72
00:02:46.020 --> 00:02:47.260
seen the good pool goggles.

73
00:02:47.260 --> 00:02:49.920
A glass-topped table sat in front of

74
00:02:49.920 --> 00:02:52.340
him, reflecting his broad shape in a softened,

75
00:02:52.480 --> 00:02:53.120
watery way.

76
00:02:53.840 --> 00:02:56.600
In the reflection, he looked almost ghostly, a

77
00:02:56.600 --> 00:02:59.100
second dog beneath the surface, watching from another

78
00:02:59.100 --> 00:02:59.480
room.

79
00:03:00.180 --> 00:03:00.940
He ignored it.

80
00:03:01.400 --> 00:03:03.400
A younger dog might have barked at himself.

81
00:03:04.160 --> 00:03:05.840
A younger dog might have tried to step

82
00:03:05.840 --> 00:03:07.820
on the table or lick the glass or

83
00:03:07.820 --> 00:03:09.540
accuse the reflection of trespassing.

84
00:03:10.200 --> 00:03:12.920
But age brings wisdom, or at least a

85
00:03:12.920 --> 00:03:13.660
tired politeness.

86
00:03:14.200 --> 00:03:15.660
He had met the dog in the table

87
00:03:15.660 --> 00:03:16.100
before.

88
00:03:16.100 --> 00:03:18.420
Neither of them was going anywhere.

89
00:03:19.180 --> 00:03:21.320
Beyond the fence, the water moved in small

90
00:03:21.320 --> 00:03:22.400
private conversations.

91
00:03:22.820 --> 00:03:24.580
A breeze passed over it, then through the

92
00:03:24.580 --> 00:03:27.200
plants, then beneath the umbrellas, then under the

93
00:03:27.200 --> 00:03:27.920
mastiff's ears.

94
00:03:28.400 --> 00:03:30.340
He lifted his nose, considering the day.

95
00:03:30.500 --> 00:03:33.640
There was damp stone, warm dust, the faint

96
00:03:33.640 --> 00:03:36.800
chemical cleanness of the pool, a flower somewhere,

97
00:03:37.480 --> 00:03:40.740
a bird with poor judgment, the memory of

98
00:03:40.740 --> 00:03:43.340
bacon from breakfast still clinging to the house,

99
00:03:43.340 --> 00:03:46.440
though breakfast itself had vanished under mysterious human

100
00:03:46.440 --> 00:03:47.180
circumstances.

101
00:03:47.820 --> 00:03:50.220
And there was something else, a sound from

102
00:03:50.220 --> 00:03:53.740
inside, not a loud sound, not yet, just

103
00:03:53.740 --> 00:03:56.440
a sliding drawer, a cabinet, the soft thump

104
00:03:56.440 --> 00:03:58.740
of a cooler being set down, the clink

105
00:03:58.740 --> 00:04:00.820
of ice, which to people meant drinks and

106
00:04:00.820 --> 00:04:02.760
to dogs meant that summer had begun arranging

107
00:04:02.760 --> 00:04:03.240
itself.

108
00:04:03.840 --> 00:04:04.680
His ears shifted.

109
00:04:05.220 --> 00:04:06.120
He did not move.

110
00:04:06.760 --> 00:04:08.420
This was the discipline of a professional.

111
00:04:09.100 --> 00:04:10.800
Inside, the people were preparing.

112
00:04:10.800 --> 00:04:12.920
They believed they were in charge of the

113
00:04:12.920 --> 00:04:13.360
afternoon.

114
00:04:13.900 --> 00:04:14.760
They had made lists.

115
00:04:15.339 --> 00:04:16.480
They had bought paper plates.

116
00:04:17.100 --> 00:04:19.720
Someone had remembered napkins, though no one would

117
00:04:19.720 --> 00:04:20.920
remember where they put them.

118
00:04:21.720 --> 00:04:24.940
Someone had said, We'll keep it simple, which

119
00:04:24.940 --> 00:04:26.700
was how people summoned complexity.

120
00:04:27.640 --> 00:04:29.560
The mastiff had seen all this before.

121
00:04:30.220 --> 00:04:31.240
Soon the gate would open.

122
00:04:31.820 --> 00:04:33.480
Voices would spill across the patio.

123
00:04:34.140 --> 00:04:35.600
Feet would slap against stone.

124
00:04:35.860 --> 00:04:38.160
The quiet lounge chairs would be claimed, abandoned,

125
00:04:38.460 --> 00:04:39.100
claimed again.

126
00:04:39.100 --> 00:04:41.500
The slide would begin its work.

127
00:04:41.980 --> 00:04:45.240
The pool would receive cannonballs, apologies, lost toys,

128
00:04:45.540 --> 00:04:47.060
and at least one adult who would insist

129
00:04:47.060 --> 00:04:49.560
the water was fine while making the face

130
00:04:49.560 --> 00:04:51.180
of a person betrayed by nature.

131
00:04:51.680 --> 00:04:53.320
And somewhere in the middle of it, someone

132
00:04:53.320 --> 00:04:56.380
would put down a plate, not carelessly, not

133
00:04:56.380 --> 00:04:59.480
exactly, just low, just for a moment.

134
00:05:00.260 --> 00:05:01.520
The mastiff blinked slowly.

135
00:05:01.920 --> 00:05:02.800
He had no plan.

136
00:05:03.140 --> 00:05:05.240
Plans were for cats and people with calendars.

137
00:05:05.800 --> 00:05:08.080
He had only a deep respect for opportunity

138
00:05:08.080 --> 00:05:11.040
and a lifetime of being underestimated by those

139
00:05:11.040 --> 00:05:12.720
who confused slowness with innocence.

140
00:05:13.960 --> 00:05:15.280
Still, that was later.

141
00:05:16.120 --> 00:05:17.680
For now, the moment held.

142
00:05:18.180 --> 00:05:20.240
The backyard seemed to belong to him alone,

143
00:05:20.580 --> 00:05:22.400
and he carried it with the solemn care

144
00:05:22.400 --> 00:05:24.560
of an old king presiding over a kingdom

145
00:05:24.560 --> 00:05:25.680
of cushions and tile.

146
00:05:26.300 --> 00:05:28.580
There was comfort in the way everything stayed

147
00:05:28.580 --> 00:05:30.640
where it had been put, the blue chairs

148
00:05:30.640 --> 00:05:32.740
in the sun, the potted plant on the

149
00:05:32.740 --> 00:05:35.560
ledge, the little dark drain in the patio

150
00:05:35.560 --> 00:05:38.460
floor, round as a button, waiting to swallow

151
00:05:38.460 --> 00:05:39.860
whatever the day spilled.

152
00:05:40.720 --> 00:05:42.580
He looked at the pool, and the pool

153
00:05:42.580 --> 00:05:43.220
looked back.

154
00:05:44.100 --> 00:05:45.680
Perhaps he was thinking of the family.

155
00:05:46.420 --> 00:05:48.240
Perhaps he was watching for the first small

156
00:05:48.240 --> 00:05:49.600
person to appear at the door.

157
00:05:50.420 --> 00:05:52.200
Perhaps he was listening for the voice that

158
00:05:52.200 --> 00:05:55.020
always called him Buddy in a tone reserved

159
00:05:55.020 --> 00:05:57.420
for both dogs and inconvenient furniture.

160
00:05:58.140 --> 00:06:00.980
Or perhaps, in the large, quiet chamber of

161
00:06:00.980 --> 00:06:03.640
his doggish heart, he understood something people often

162
00:06:03.640 --> 00:06:06.840
miss while setting out cups, that every ordinary

163
00:06:06.840 --> 00:06:09.200
day has a small hinge hidden inside it.

164
00:06:09.780 --> 00:06:10.500
A door opens.

165
00:06:10.880 --> 00:06:11.740
A child laughs.

166
00:06:12.320 --> 00:06:13.440
Ice shifts in a cooler.

167
00:06:13.920 --> 00:06:16.040
A wet hand lands on an old dog's

168
00:06:16.040 --> 00:06:16.340
head.

169
00:06:16.900 --> 00:06:18.340
Nothing grand announces itself.

170
00:06:18.480 --> 00:06:19.920
No trumpet sounds over the patio.

171
00:06:20.480 --> 00:06:22.440
The umbrellas do not unfurl in recognition.

172
00:06:23.040 --> 00:06:24.340
The slide does not bow.

173
00:06:24.740 --> 00:06:25.860
But the day changes.

174
00:06:26.480 --> 00:06:28.380
So he waited on the middle cushion, where

175
00:06:28.380 --> 00:06:30.460
he could see nearly everything, and guarded the

176
00:06:30.460 --> 00:06:31.620
blue water from silence.

177
00:06:31.620 --> 00:06:34.060
And when the first voice finally called from

178
00:06:34.060 --> 00:06:35.200
inside, where is he?

179
00:06:35.760 --> 00:06:37.720
The old mastiff did not turn around.

180
00:06:38.120 --> 00:06:40.520
He only wagged his tail once, against the

181
00:06:40.520 --> 00:06:40.780
wicker.

182
00:06:41.420 --> 00:06:42.620
A soft royal knock.

183
00:06:43.040 --> 00:06:44.000
The kingdom was open.
